      <bioghist id="aspace_73612535061b3e30dab0630192acc2ee">
         <head>Biographical Note</head>
         <p>Lord Edward William Pelham-Clinton (August 11, 1836-July 9, 1907), after receiving his
            education at Eton, served in the military at Crimea, India and Canada, eventually
            reaching the rank of Lieutenant Colonel. From 1881 to 1894, Pelham-Clinton served as
            Groom-in-waiting to Queen Victoria. Consequently he acted as Master of the Household
            from 1894 until her death. Pelham-Clinton received two of the most top honors in
            Britain: Knight Commander of the Most Honourable Order of the Bath and Knight Grand
            Cross of the Royal Victorian Order.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_fb72073fe0f91375a12b51b7a0fe00b4">
         <head>Collection Overview</head>
         <p>Collection houses the papers of Lord Edward William Pelham-Clinton, including
            recollections of Queen Victoria and Edward VII, diaries, and autograph albums.</p>
      </scopecontent>
